<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8BE16F7CD8F8501116FEBC" blockId="2.[136,1452,1996,2059]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,256]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="168" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
The type is characterized by whitish thallus with semiglobose, in part sorediate, scattered or crowded warts. The thallus is zoned at the margin. Soralia with granular soredia are very frequent, whitish to greenish grey (
<figureCitation id="131D2A59FF8BE16E78FCF86C1673F7B7" box="[1196,1293,2032,2059]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,234,1136,1158]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1112]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1436,190,1112]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lectotype of Pertusaria jurana in HBG." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423925" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423925/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). The analysis of secondary metabolites (
<collectionCode id="ED37AE19FF8AE16F7DFBFF02129DFF04" box="[427,483,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">TLC</collectionCode>
) showed the presence of fatty acids. 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7F29FF03173FFF04" box="[889,1089,159,184]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jurana">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7F29FF03173FFF04" box="[889,1089,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Pertusaria jurana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF8AE16F7976FF0216D2FF04" box="[1318,1452,158,184]" name="Switzerland" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
and the name has later been reported from Europe only (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7EA4FF5E10E8FF61" author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[756,918,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="321 - 701" refId="ref2932" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1935 [1936]) Pertusariacae. In: Zahlbruckner, A. (ed.) Dr. L. Rabenhorsts Kryptogamenflora von Deutchland, Osterreich und der Schweiz. Leipzig, Akademische Verlagsgesellschaft. 9 (5) [1]: 321 - 701." type="journal article" year="1935">Erichsen 1935</bibRefCitation>
[
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7FF3FF5E109CFF61" author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[931,994,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="77 - 101" refId="ref2989" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1936) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flechtengattung Pertusaria. Feddes Repertorium 41: 77 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410105" type="journal article" year="1936">1936</bibRefCitation>
]; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7FA4FF5F17AFFF61" author="Hocevar, S. &amp; Batic, F. &amp; Piskernik, M. &amp; Martincic, A." box="[1012,1233,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="319" refId="ref3194" refString="Hocevar, S., Batic, F., Piskernik, M. &amp; Martincic, A. (1995) Glive v pragozdovih Slovenije. Strokovna in znanstvena dela 117. Gozdarski Institut Slovenije, Ljubljana, p. 319." type="book chapter" year="1995">
