<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7E0EFAA411C4FAF1" box="[606,698,1336,1357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">confluens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in HBG.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8AE16F7CEDFAE113BEFA62" blockId="3.[136,1452,1404,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">
It is chemically and morphologically concordant with the present circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F78D9FAE11209FA06" authority="(Hudson 1762: 445) Hafellner" authorityName="Hafellner" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" baseAuthorityPageNumber="445" baseAuthorityYear="1762" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Lepra" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="albescens">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F78D9FAE1163CFA2A" box="[1161,1346,1404,1430]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Lepra albescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7902FAE01383FA07" author="Hudson, W." pageId="3" pageNumber="168" refId="ref3237" refString="Hudson, W. (1762) Flora Anglica. Hertfordshire Natural History Society and Field Club, Impensis auctoris 536 pp." type="book" year="1762">Hudson 1762: 445</bibRefCitation>
) Hafellner
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7DF8FA3C118AFA06" author="Hafellner, J. &amp; Turk, R." box="[424,756,1440,1466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 216" refId="ref3105" refString="Hafellner, J. &amp; Turk, R. (2016) Die lichenisierten Pilze Osterreichs-eine neue Checkliste der bisher nachgewiesenen Taxa mit Angaben zur Verbreitung und Substratokologie. Stapfia 104 (1): 1 - 216." type="journal article" year="2016">
Hafellner &amp; 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF8AE16F7E69FA3C110CFA06" box="[569,626,1440,1466]" name="Turks and Caicos Islands" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Türk</collectingCountry>
, 2016: 171
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7F5CFA3C1778FA06" author="Chambers, S. P. &amp; Gilbert, O. L. &amp; James, P. W. &amp; Aptroot, A. &amp; Purvis, O. W." box="[780,1030,1440,1466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="673 - 687" refId="ref2603" refString="Chambers, S. P., Gilbert, O. L., James, P. W., Aptroot, A. &amp; Purvis, O. W. (2009) Pertusaria DC. (1805). In: Smith, C. W., Aptroot, A., Coppins, B. J., Fletcher, A., Gilbert, O. L., James, P. W. &amp; Wolseley, P. A. (Eds.) The Lichens of Great Britain and Ireland. British Lichen Society, the Natural History Museum, London, pp. 673 - 687." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Chambers 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7FD9FA3D10BDFA06" box="[905,963,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) and is thus considered synonymous here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8AE16F7CEDFA751167F92E" blockId="3.[136,1452,1404,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">
In the protologue Erichsen cited 
<specimenCount id="9D20FD55FF8AE16F7E69FA741198F9BE" box="[569,742,1512,1538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7F40FA7510A3F9BE" box="[784,989,1513,1538]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jurana">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7F40FA7510A3F9BE" box="[784,989,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Pertusaria jurana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but did not determine any specimen as a 
<typeStatus id="549D887EFF8AE16F7CCFF990127BF99A" box="[159,261,1548,1574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">holotype</typeStatus>
. Three of them are deposited in 
<collectionCode id="ED37AE19FF8AE16F7ED3F99011BCF99A" box="[643,706,1548,1574]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/fv5j-intd" name="Hiroshima Botanical Garden" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">HBG</collectionCode>
. One sheet collected from Schwiez is annotated as ‘Typus’ with handwritten notes of Erichsen and in this case it should be designated as 
<typeStatus id="549D887EFF8AE16F7F92F9AC1757F9F6" box="[962,1065,1584,1610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7867F9AC1668F9F6" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1079,1302,1584,1610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="159" refId="ref4129" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal article" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F78C9F9AD17ACF9F6" box="[1177,1234,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7CD8F9C9122DF9D2" box="[136,339,1621,1646]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jurana">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7CD8F9C9122DF9D2" box="[136,339,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Pertusaria jurana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of two pieces of bark with the same thallus. Morphological characters of both correspond to the description in the protolouge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6557FF8AE16F7CEDF90111CFF80E" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8AE16F7CEDF9011657F89F" blockId="3.[136,1452,1404,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7CEDF9011203F90A" authorityName="Hafellner" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" baseAuthorityYear="1762" box="[189,381,1692,1718]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Lepra" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="albescens">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7CEDF9011203F90A" box="[189,381,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Lepra albescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be mistaken for the chemically and, when young, also morphologically similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F79C5F90111FEF966" authority="(Nylander 1861: 180) Hafellner" authorityName="Hafellner" baseAuthorityName="Nylander" baseAuthorityPageNumber="180" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Lepra" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ophthalmiza">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F79C5F901126CF966" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">L. ophthalmiza</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7D72F95C1178F966" author="Nylander, W." box="[290,518,1728,1754]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 312" refId="ref3486" refString="Nylander, W. (1861) Lichenes Scandinaviae sive prodromus lichenographiae Scandinaviae. Notiser ur Sallskapets pro Fauna et Flora Fennica Forhandlingar 5: 1 - 312" type="journal article" year="1861">Nylander 1861: 180</bibRefCitation>
) Hafellner
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7EFEF95C1089F966" author="Hafellner, J. &amp; Turk, R." box="[686,1015,1728,1754]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 216" refId="ref3105" refString="Hafellner, J. &amp; Turk, R. (2016) Die lichenisierten Pilze Osterreichs-eine neue Checkliste der bisher nachgewiesenen Taxa mit Angaben zur Verbreitung und Substratokologie. Stapfia 104 (1): 1 - 216." type="journal article" year="2016">
Hafellner &amp; 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF8AE16F7F6DF95C1008F966" box="[829,886,1728,1754]" name="Turks and Caicos Islands" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Türk</collectingCountry>
, 2016: 173
</bibRefCitation>
). Both species produce fatty acids, but they predominantly differ in the thallus characters: 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7E9CF9791029F942" authorityName="Hafellner" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" baseAuthorityYear="1762" box="[716,855,1764,1790]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Lepra" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="albescens">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7E9CF9791029F942" box="[716,855,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">L. albescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produces true soralia with granular soredia, whereas the sorediate warts of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7D2FF8951159F89E" authorityName="Hafellner" baseAuthorityName="Nylander" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[383,551,1800,1826]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Lepra" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ophthalmiza">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7D2FF8951159F89E" box="[383,551,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">L. ophthalmiza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contain apothecia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7F52F8941094F89E" author="Oset, M. &amp; Kukwa, M." box="[770,1002,1800,1826]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="231 - 238" refId="ref3579" refString="Oset, M. &amp; Kukwa, M. (2010) The lichen genus Pertusaria in Poland I. P. multipuncta and P. ophthalmiza. Acta Mycologica 45 (2): 231 - 238. https: // doi. org / 10.5586 / am. 2010.028" type="journal article" year="2010">Oset &amp; Kukwa 2010</bibRefCitation>
and literature cited therein).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8AE16F7CEDF8B011CFF80E" blockId="3.[136,1452,1404,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">
Another similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8AE16F7DA1F8B1108FF8FB" authority="Archer et al. (2009: 316)" authorityName="Archer" authorityPageNumber="316" authorityYear="2009" box="[497,1009,1836,1863]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="krogiae">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7DA1F8B111B9F8FA" box="[497,711,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Pertusaria krogiae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7E9FF8B0108FF8FB" author="Archer, A. W. &amp; Elix, J. &amp; Fischer, E. &amp; Killmann, D. &amp; Serusiaux, E." box="[719,1009,1836,1863]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="309 - 333" refId="ref2455" refString="Archer, A. W., Elix, J. A, Fischer, E., Killmann, D. &amp; Serusiaux, E. (2009) The lichen genus Pertusaria (Ascomycota) in Central Africa (Congo / Kivu, Rwanda and Burundi) and Western Kenya. Nova Hedwigia 88 (3 - 4): 309 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / 0029 - 5035 / 2009 / 0088 - 0309" type="journal article" year="2009">
Archer 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7F76F8B1101FF8FA" box="[806,865,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
(2009: 316)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F78C1F8B01615F8FA" author="Archer, A. W. &amp; Elix, J. &amp; Fischer, E. &amp; Killmann, D. &amp; Serusiaux, E." box="[1169,1387,1836,1862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="309 - 333" refId="ref2455" refString="Archer, A. W., Elix, J. A, Fischer, E., Killmann, D. &amp; Serusiaux, E. (2009) The lichen genus Pertusaria (Ascomycota) in Central Africa (Congo / Kivu, Rwanda and Burundi) and Western Kenya. Nova Hedwigia 88 (3 - 4): 309 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / 0029 - 5035 / 2009 / 0088 - 0309" type="journal article" year="2009">
Archer 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F78BAF8B1165BF8FA" box="[1258,1317,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). The species is characterized by a grey thallus with numerous grey-whitish, raised to subtuberculate soralia; and the presence of lichesterinic, protolichesterinic and allo-protolichesterinic acids and sometimes atranorin. All species listed above are corticolous (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7D6CF80412B5F80E" author="Hanko, B." box="[316,459,1944,1970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 297" refId="ref3144" refString="Hanko, B. (1983) Die Chemotypen der Flechtengattung Pertusaria in Europa. Bibliotheca Lichenologic 19: 1 - 297." type="journal article" year="1983">Hanko 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8AE16F7D85F80411D8F80E" author="Archer, A. W. &amp; Elix, J. &amp; Fischer, E. &amp; Killmann, D. &amp; Serusiaux, E." box="[469,678,1944,1970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="309 - 333" refId="ref2455" refString="Archer, A. W., Elix, J. A, Fischer, E., Killmann, D. &amp; Serusiaux, E. (2009) The lichen genus Pertusaria (Ascomycota) in Central Africa (Congo / Kivu, Rwanda and Burundi) and Western Kenya. Nova Hedwigia 88 (3 - 4): 309 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / 0029 - 5035 / 2009 / 0088 - 0309" type="journal article" year="2009">
Archer 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8AE16F7E7AF805111CF80E" box="[554,610,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
